**24.** A person deposited Tk. $1,000$ in a bank for $4$ years. The bank will pay him interest at a rate of $10\%$ for the first $2$ years and at a rate of $5\%$ for the last $2$ years. How much money will the person receive at the end of $4$ years?<br>
[BADC (Admin Officer)-2020]

+++ Solution:
$\text{Interest for first 2 years} = (1000 \times 10 \times 2) / 100 = 200$

$\text{Interest for last 2 years} = (1000 \times 5 \times 2) / 100 = 100$

$\text{Total Interest} = 200 + 100 = 300$

$\text{Total Amount} = 1000 + 300 = 1300$
+++

